---
description: Rules for EDA, feature engineering, and modeling
alwaysApply: false
---

For data science tasks:

Structure:
- Use notebooks for EDA, feature engineering decisions, modeling, and reporting analysis
- Keep notebook sections clear, reproducible, and presentation-ready
- Avoid duplicating preprocessing logic unnecessarily across notebooks

EDA:
- Include data quality checks
- Include target distribution analysis
- Include univariate and bivariate analysis
- Add short markdown interpretations for important charts
- Separate observations from hypotheses

Modeling:
- Start with a simple baseline model
- Use proper train/validation/test discipline
- Preserve target class proportions during splitting
- Compare models fairly
- Evaluate on holdout data
- Present model comparisons with organized tables and clear charts
- Make the final model and threshold choice explicit
- Include feature importance or equivalent interpretation for the final selected model
- Include threshold analysis when relevant
- Report limitations clearly

Always check:
- target leakage
- class imbalance
- missing values
- categorical encoding consistency
- reproducibility via random seeds